sentences.english: I don’t mind really if millionaires vote against me.
sentences.chinese: 我真的不介意百万富翁投反对票反对我。

sentences.english: “The members who voted no will have some culpability, ” he said.
sentences.chinese: “投反对票的议员要承担一些罪责，”他说。

sentences.english: The Slovakian parliament has just voted this down, although it is likely to accept it in the end.
sentences.chinese: 斯洛伐克议会投了反对票，但接受似乎只是时间问题。

sentences.english: The Republican commissioners were the two dissenters.
sentences.chinese: 投反对票的是两位共和党委员。

sentences.english: Will you blackball her if she tries to join our club?
sentences.chinese: 假如她要参加我们的俱乐部，你是否投反对票？

sentences.english: Our senator voted against that bill.
sentences.chinese: 我们这个区对这个法案投了反对票。

sentences.english: She never knew why they blackballed her from the club.
sentences.chinese: 她从不知道为什么他们投反对票阻止她加入俱乐部。

sentences.english: That is why I voted against him.
sentences.chinese: 这就是我对他投了反对票的原因。

definition: abbr. for 參議院|参议院[can1 yi4 yuan4], senate/upper chamber (of legislative assembly)
